                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" id="aesopsfables_sng_1" hclass="sense"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a collection of short stories about animals which behave in a human way. Each story teaches a moral lesson. They are said to be by a Greek called Aesop who lived in the 6th century BC, but many of them are much older than this. Well-known stories include <span class="ebi"><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-tortoise-and-the-hare" title="The Tortoise and the Hare definition"><span class="ndv">The Tortoise and the Hare</span></a></span> and <span class="ebi">The Fox and the Grapes</span>.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
